quran[54]{c,v,t}:
  70,19,"Verily, man is by nature rash"
  70,20,"when evil touches him, very impatient"
  70,21,"when good touches him, niggardly"
  70,22,all save those who pray
  70,23,who remain at their prayers
  70,24,and in whose wealth is a reasonable due (set aside)
  70,25,for him who asks and him who is kept from asking
  70,26,and those who believe in a day of judgment
  70,27,and those who shrink in terror from the torment of their Lord
  70,28,"verily, the torment of their Lord is not safe"
  70,29,and those who guard their private parts
  70,30,"except for their wives or the (slave girls) whom their right hands possess, for they are not to be blamed"
  70,31,"but whoso craves beyond this, they are the transgressors"
  70,32,and those who observe their trusts and their compacts
  70,33,and those who are upright in their testimonies
  70,34,and those who keep their prayers
  70,35,these shall dwell in gardens honoured
  70,36,What ails the misbelievers that they hurry on before thee
  70,37,crowding together on the right and on the left
  70,38,Does every man of them wish to enter the garden of pleasure
  70,39,"Nay, we created them of what they know"
  70,40,"And I need not swear by the Lord of the easts and the wests; verily, we are able"
  70,41,"to change them for others better, nor are we prevented"
  70,42,"So leave them to plunge in discussion, and to play until they meet that day of theirs which they are threatened with"
  70,43,"the day when they shall come forth in haste from the graves, as though they flock to a standard"
  70,44,with their looks abashed; meanness shall cover them! That is the day which they were promised
  71,1,"Verily, we sent Noah to his people, 'Warn thy people before there come to them a grievous torment"
  71,2,"Said he, 'O my people! verily, I am to you an obvious warner"
  71,3,that ye serve God and fear Him and obey me
  71,4,"He will pardon you your sins, and will defer you unto an appointed time; verily, God's appointed time when it comes will not be deferred, did ye but know"
  71,5,"Said he, 'My Lord! verily, I have called my people by night and day"
  71,6,and my call did but increase them in flight
  71,7,"and, verily, every time I called them, that Thou mightest pardon them, they placed their fingers in their ears and tried to cover themselves with their garments and persisted, and were very big with pride"
  71,8,Then I called them openly
  71,9,then I published to them and I spoke to them in secret
  71,10,"and I said, \"Ask forgiveness of your Lord, verily, He is very forgiving"
  71,11,He will send the rain upon you in torrents
  71,12,"and will extend to you wealth and children, and will make for you gardens, and will make for you rivers"
  71,13,What ails you that ye hope not for something serious from God
  71,14,when He has created you by steps
  71,15,Do ye not see how God has created the seven heavens in stories
  71,16,"and has set the moon therein for a light, and set the sun for a lamp"
  71,17,and God has made you grow out of the earth
  71,18,"and then He will make you return thereto, and will make you come forth therefrom"
  71,19,and God has made for you the earth a carpet
  71,20,that ye may walk therein in broad paths
  71,21,"Said Noah, 'My Lord! verily, they have rebelled against me, and followed him whose wealth and children have but added to his loss"
  71,22,and they have plotted a great plot
  71,23,"and said, \"Ye shall surely not leave your gods: ye shall surely neither leave Wadd, nor Suwah, nor Yaghuth, nor Ya'uq, nor Nasr"
  71,24,"and they led astray many.\"' And thou (Mohammed) wilt only increase the unjust in their error"
  71,25,"because of their sins they were drowned and made to enter into the fire, and they found no helpers against God"
  71,26,"And Noah said, 'My Lord! leave not upon the earth one dweller of the misbelievers"
  71,27,"Verily, Thou, if Thou shouldst leave them, they will lead astray Thy servants, and they will only bear for children sinners and misbelievers"
  71,28,"My Lord! pardon me and my two parents, and whomsoever enters my house believing, and (pardon) the believers men and women - but Thou shalt only increase the unjust in loss"